wikipedia_page.main: James Caine (24 June 1908 – 9 May 1971) was an English professional footballer who played as a central defender. He was on the books of three Football League clubs, but only played in the first-team for Nelson, where he made five league appearances. After leaving Bury in 1932, he spent some time in non-league football, before retiring to work in a factory.

response: Caine was born on 20 June 1936 in Nelson, Lancashire, in north-west England. He is one of six sons of former professional footballer James Caine, who played as a defender for Nelson in the Football League in the late 1920s.
